<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-10-17T04:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-10-17T04:00:00-05:00" n="236" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d236">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00B/650: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-10-17T17:00:00+08:00">October 17, 1929—5
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 5:05 p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>896. Following from American Consul at Harbin: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>“October 16, 10 a.m. Verdict case 38 prisoners Soviet Consulate
                                    raid given out in prison yesterday. Five sentenced to nine
                                    years, 21 to seven, 7 to five and 4 (women) to two. Chinese
                                    interpreter freed. Local foreign opinion is that trial was a
                                    farce.”</p>
                            </quote></p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">MacMurray</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>